{"lemma":"دانِقَيْ","slug":"دانِقَيْ","root":"د.ن.ق","root_slug":"د-ن-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ن-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13214","n13215"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90%D9%82%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"any of several coins, daniq, originally a sixth of a dirham"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"any of several weight measures"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a linear measure, ¹⁄₆ of a قِيرَاط (qīrāṭ) – 29.17 m²","tags":["Egypt","Medieval"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Middle Persian [Term?] (/⁠dānaq⁠/) (Persian دانگ (dâng, literally “sixth”))."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13214","headword_ar":"دَانَقٌ","root":"dnq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n13215","headword_ar":"دَانِقٌ","root":"dnq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Foolish; stupid; having little,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no, intellect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"understanding:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAy^iqN","text_ar":"دَايِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thief."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, Ibn-'Abbád, K, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Emaciated and falling down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emaciated and tottering;"},{"kind":"text","text":"expl. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mahozuwlN saAqiTN","text_ar":"مَهْزُولٌ سَاقِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AA, S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"falling down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tottering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAqiTN","text_ar":"سَاقِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of emaciation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK:) applied to a man (AA, K) and to a she-camel. (K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having a constant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chronic, disease, and oppressed thereby so as to be at the point of death."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, TA.)       -A2-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAnaqa","text_ar":"دَانَقَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S, Mgh, Msb, K,) the former, accord. to some, the more chaste, arabicized [from the Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAnok","text_ar":"دَانْك"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAnak","text_ar":"دَانَك"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAnaAqN","text_ar":"دَانَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S, K,) like as they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dirohamN","text_ar":"دِرْهَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dirohaAmN","text_ar":"دِرْهَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) [but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAnaAqN","text_ar":"دَانَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"seems to have been disallowed by Sb, either as unused or as post-classical,] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sixth part of a dirhem"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drachm"},{"kind":"text","text":"); (S, Msb, K;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two carats;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two grains of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuronuwb","text_ar":"خُرْنُوب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carob"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the ancient Greeks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the dirhem with them was twelve grains of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xrnwb","text_ar":"خرنوب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dAnq","text_ar":"دانق"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the Muslims is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two grains of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xrnwb","text_ar":"خرنوب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and two thirds of a grain of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xrnwb","text_ar":"خرنوب"},{"kind":"text","text":", for the dirhem of the Muslims is sixteen grains of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xrnwb","text_ar":"خرنوب"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sixth part of the deenár:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA: [but this I find nowhere else: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diynaArN","text_ar":"دِينَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riTolN","text_ar":"رِطْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dAnq","text_ar":"دانق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dawaAniqu","text_ar":"دَوَانِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dawaAniyqu","text_ar":"دَوَانِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, TA;) the former is said by Az to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAniqN","text_ar":"دَانِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the latter, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAnaqN","text_ar":"دَانَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and it is said that every pl. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawaAEilu","text_ar":"فَوَاعِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafaAEilu","text_ar":"مَفَاعِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be lengthened with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"so that one may say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawaAEiylu","text_ar":"فَوَاعِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafaAEiylu","text_ar":"مَفَاعِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or, accord. to Sb,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dawaAniyqu","text_ar":"دَوَانِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAnaAqN","text_ar":"دَانَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", though this be not in their speech. (TA.) [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A small silver coin, the sixth part of the coin called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diroham","text_ar":"دِرْهَم"},{"kind":"text","text":".] The dim. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwayoniyqN","text_ar":"دُوَيْنِيقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","AA","S","JK","Mgh","Msb"]}]}}